main event: A circular flame-colored object was reported hovering overhead in Baltimore, Maryland on June 7, 1956.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 5 minutes., The object was described as circular and flame-colored., Investigators noted the absence of direct eyewitness accounts due to insufficient information., A possible correlation was suggested with another case (MATS CASE 0775)., No photographs were available, and the report included sketches instead.
witness description: Observers unknown & insufficient information to evaluate.
